  <mads:note type="source">Brill's New Pauly: "Cassius Felix, Physician and translator, 5th cent.
      AD, Physician from Cirta, translator of Greek language medical writings, wrote or translated
      in AD 447 for his son a piece of writing titled De medicina, later used by Isidor (Orig.
      4,8,4). ....f all Latin authors of medical writings, he makes the most frequent use of Galen
      and writings from the Hippocratic tradition"....Nutton, Vivian (London).  Cassius." Brill's New Pauly. Antiquity volumes edited by: Hubert Cancik and Helmuth Schneider . Brill, 2008. Brill Online. Tufts University Library. 30 December 2008</mads:note>
